¼This flowerbed
was added to this lovely garden
by
Forward 4 Work
(helping local people with disabilities into work)
on Rosie Day 12th May 2009.
These flowers have been planted in
loving memory of those we have lost and for the
wonderful work of nurses everywhere on
International Nurses Day."╗
ĖJanina Koniuszewska

In loving memory
of our dear mum.
Sadly missed.
always remembered.

Passed away July 1996

I sit and wait just lonely me,
Beneath the branches of your tree,
The sun shines warm,
A gentle breeze carries the sweet
fragrance of flowers in the air,
A leaf falls and tangles in my hair.
I'm feeling melancholy, I sigh,
As tear drops quickly fill my eyes,
Suddenly you flutter by,
Oh my beautiful butterfly."▀
▄I'm loving memory of James Robert Murphy
22nd February 1995 - 25th September 2015
First class philosophy student, football player and founder of the Philosophy team,
treasured brother, son and friend, who gave his life to save another.
"Love: it will not betray, dismay, or enslave you. It will set you free, to be the man you were made to be.""¾
